== Short Bio 
Jiaming is a postdoctoral researcher at Yale CS department, under the supervision of [http://www.cs.yale.edu/homes/wibisono/ Andre Wibisono].
#He is also a tenure-track assistant professor (on leave) in the [https://sds.cuhk.edu.cn/en School of Data Science] at The Chinese University of Hong Kong, Shenzhen. 
Previously, he obtained Ph.D. in Operations Research at Georgia Tech, advised by [https://www2.isye.gatech.edu/~monteiro/ Renato Monteiro]. 
#He holds a master's degree in computational science and engineering. 
#As an undergrad, he studied ocean engineering and applied math in Shanghai Jiao Tong University.
# where he worked on applications of the [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Homotopy_analysis_method homotopy analysis method] with [http://naoce.sjtu.edu.cn/en/teachershow.aspx?info_lb=20&info_id=93&flag=2 Prof. Zhiliang Lin].
== Research Interests 
His primary research goal is to design, analyze and implement fast algorithms for solving a general class of problems in data science. His research interests broadly include topics in optimization and sampling algorithms, such as
- Convex and Nonconvex Optimization
- Nonsmooth Optimization
- Stochastic Optimization
- High-dimensional Sampling Algorithms
- Foundation of Data Science
